Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spread squash in 13x9-inch microwavable dish. Add 2 tablespoons water and season with salt. Cover with plastic wrap, folding back 1 corner 1/4-inch to vent steam. Microwave on High 5minutes. Stir, cover and microwave on High an additional 2 minutes or until squash is very tender. Mash squash with milk, sugar, 2 tablespoons of the melted butter and pumpkin pie spice. Mix in eggs. Toss cookie crumbs and remaining butter. Sprinkle over squash. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until squash is set and crumbs are brown.